## Supabase (`public`) — planning + recall (not the same as D1 memory)

Worker code **`mirrorAgentsamD1PlanToSupabasePublic`** (scheduled on plan/task writes and `executePlan`) upserts **`public.agentsam_plans`** / **`public.agentsam_plan_tasks`** from D1. For manual repair or Cursor-only sessions, you can still run MCP SQL; failures there do not patch D1.

| D1 | Supabase `public` | Notes |
|----|-------------------|--------|
| `agentsam_plans` | `agentsam_plans` | PG has fewer columns (no `tenant_id` / `plan_type` on plans). Sync `id`, `plan_date`, `title`, `status`, `session_notes`, `tasks_total` / `tasks_done` / `tasks_blocked`, timestamps. |
| `agentsam_plan_tasks` | `agentsam_plan_tasks` | PG has no `output_summary`; map D1 `output_summary` → **`notes`**. `completed_at` is `timestamptz` — use `to_timestamp(d1_unix)`. |
| `agentsam_memory` (key/value) | **`agent_memory`** (role/content/embedding) | Different models: use **`agent_memory`** for session summaries tied to `match_agent_memory`. Dedupe with `metadata->>'sync_key'` (delete then insert, or a stable key). |

Project: **inneranimalmedia-business-supabase** (`dpmuvynqixblxsilnlut`). The Worker maps columns in **`mapD1PlanToSupabasePublicRow`** / **`mapD1PlanTaskToSupabasePublicRow`**; use MCP SQL only for **one-off repair** if the mirror drifts.

